"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417582","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-14","<p>A copy of the Army Reserve Order of Battle has been placed in the Library of the House and is attached.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-09-14T15:52:20.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417582/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417582/answer","20150909_PQ_07782_75656_Reserve_Order_Battle_Soames_Reserves_ORBAT_UNCLASS[1].pdf","9578 - Army Reserve Order of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417582/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-08","Army Reserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library a copy of the Army Reserve's Order of Battle.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","9578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417583","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>A number of engineering graduates and apprentices are recruited each year to the Ministry of Defence (MOD)'s civilian workforce and trained as nuclear specialists. This is supplemented by lateral entry of personnel with established nuclear skills, including engineers from the wider market and former Royal Navy personnel.</p><p>The Government recognises that both the civil and Defence Nuclear Programmes must be sustained. I have discussed this issue with Ministerial colleagues from other Government Departments over the last year and the Government's approach to generating the skills needed was published in &quot;Sustaining Our Nuclear Skills&quot; on 20 March 2015, available at the following link: http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/sustaining-our-nuclear-skills. MOD officials attend the Nuclear Industry Council and the Nuclear Owner's Group at which these issues are discussed with representatives of both the civil and defence industry.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","9574","2015-09-15T15:08:36.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417583/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417583/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417583/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-08","Nuclear Engineering: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to recruit nuclear engineers from the civil sector; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","9579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417584","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>The value of Ministry of Defence (MOD) contracts placed in each of the last five years where work is undertaken in the Argyll and Bute constituency is provided below. The analysis includes work undertaken at Her Majesty's Naval Base (HMNB) Clyde, but excludes work undertaken at HMNB Clyde under the Â£2.6 billion Maritime Support Delivery Framework with Babcock, as the work is split between HMNBs Devonport and Clyde.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Current total value of contracts (Â£ million)</strong></p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>11.9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>0.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>171.4*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>40.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>19.5</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>* The large increase in 2012-13 is due to a Â£162.2 million contract with AWE for Strategic Weapon Support.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-09-15T15:12:34.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417584/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417584/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417584/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-08","Defence: Argyll and Bute","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the total value of defence-related contracts placed by his Department with suppliers based in Argyll and Bute constituency was in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","9570"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417585","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) annually publishes estimates of defence spending by the Top 15 World-wide military spenders. The MOD's Annual Statistical Series 1 Finance Bulletin 1.02 on International Defence published on 14 August 2014, (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/international-defence-expenditure-2014--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/international-defence-expenditure-2014--2</a>) estimates China's Defence Expenditure in 2013 to be US$275 billion based on Purchasing Power Parity (PPP) rates. This estimate is calculated from defence expenditure data published by Stockholm International Peace Research Institute (SIPRI) data and PPP rates published by the International Monetary Fund (IMF).</p><p>On 8 October 2015 the MOD will publish updated estimates covering 2014, which will be based on the latest available SIPRI data.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-09-14T15:54:06.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417585/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417585/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417585/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-08","Defence: China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will make an estimate of Chinese defence expenditure on a Purchasing Power Parity basis; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","9573"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417586","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>A number of engineering graduates and apprentices are recruited each year to the Ministry of Defence (MOD)'s civilian workforce and trained as nuclear specialists. This is supplemented by lateral entry of personnel with established nuclear skills, including engineers from the wider market and former Royal Navy personnel.</p><p>The Government recognises that both the civil and Defence Nuclear Programmes must be sustained. I have discussed this issue with Ministerial colleagues from other Government Departments over the last year and the Government's approach to generating the skills needed was published in &quot;Sustaining Our Nuclear Skills&quot; on 20 March 2015, available at the following link: http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/sustaining-our-nuclear-skills. MOD officials attend the Nuclear Industry Council and the Nuclear Owner's Group at which these issues are discussed with representatives of both the civil and defence industry.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","9579","2015-09-15T15:08:36.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417586/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417586/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417586/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-08","Nuclear Engineering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with (a) Ministerial colleagues and (b) the civil nuclear industry on the provision of nuclear engineers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","9574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417587","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-16","<p>In Financial Year (FY) 2005-06, the Ministry of Defence (MOD) made Recruitment and Retention Allowance (RRA) payments of Â£1.3 million to civilian Nuclear Suitably Qualified and Experienced Personnel (NSQEP). Payment information for subsequent financial years for civilian personnel until 2014-15 could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Not all NSQEP are nuclear engineers; staff in receipt of NSQEP include personnel in other functions such as project management and logistics.</p><p> </p><p>The following table provides the total Recruitment and Retention Payments paid specifically to military nuclear engineers.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>FY</strong></p><p><strong>2007-08</strong></p><p><strong>Â£ millions</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY</strong></p><p><strong>2008-09</strong></p><p><strong>Â£ millions</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY</strong></p><p><strong>2009-10</strong></p><p><strong>Â£ millions</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY</strong></p><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p><p><strong>Â£ millions</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY</strong></p><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p><p><strong>Â£ millions</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY</strong></p><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p><p><strong>Â£ millions</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY</strong></p><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p><p><strong>Â£ millions</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY</strong></p><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p><p><strong>Â£ millions</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nuclear</p><p>Propulsion</p><p>Pay</p></td><td><p>Â£2.9</p></td><td><p>Â£2.8</p></td><td><p>Â£3.2</p></td><td><p>Â£3.3</p></td><td><p>Â£3.6</p></td><td><p>Â£3.6</p></td><td><p>Â£3.4</p></td><td><p>Â£3.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Financial</p><p>Retention</p><p>Incentive</p></td><td><p>Â£0.7</p></td><td><p>Â£1.9</p></td><td><p>Â£1.9</p></td><td><p>Â£1.4</p></td><td><p>Â£0.2</p></td><td><p>Â£0.8</p></td><td