"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417589","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State for Defence and Ministry of Defence officials regularly meet with a range of external organisations to discuss the Government's objectives in Europe. Details of Ministerial meetings with external organisations are published quarterly at the following link: https://www.gov.uk/search?q=Ministerial+meetings+with+external+organisations.</p><p> </p><p>Government Departments are appropriately resourced to support the Government's priorities in Europe.</p><p> </p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","9498 ; 9534","2015-09-15T15:09:19.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417589/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417589/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417589/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-08","Ministry of Defence: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which external organisations officials in his Department have met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many meetings such officials have had with each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9516"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417590","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-16","<p>It has been the policy of successive Governments not to comment on the employment of UK intelligence or surveillance capabilities.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-09-16T14:12:55.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417590/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417590/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417590/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-08","Armed Forces: Russia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assets are monitoring the deployment of Severomorsk to the Arctic Ocean.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","9425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417591","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>The following assets were involved in the exercises Android Preference in 2014 and Triplex Warrior 2015:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>2014 Ex Android Preference</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015 Ex Triplex Warrior</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>RAF</strong></p></td><td><p>Typhoon</p><p>Tornado</p><p>E-3D Sentry</p><p>Sentinel</p><p>Voyager</p><p>Hawk</p><p>UK Air Surveillance and</p><p>Control System</p></td><td><p>Typhoon</p><p>Tornado</p><p>E-3D Sentry</p><p>Sentinel</p><p>Voyager</p><p>Hawk</p><p>UK Air Surveillance and Control System</p><p>Chinook</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Navy</strong></p></td><td><p>Sea King</p><p>Type-45</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Army</strong></p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td><td><p>Joint Tactical Air Controllers (JTAC)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>NATO</strong></p></td><td><p>United States Air Force (USAF) F-15C</p><p>USAF F-15E</p><p>USAF 321<sup>st</sup> Special</p><p>Tactics Squadron</p><p>Royal Netherlands Air Force (RNLAF)</p><p>F-16AM</p></td><td><p>USAF F-15C</p><p>USAF F-15E</p><p>USAF KC-135</p><p>USAF F-22A</p><p>USAF C-17</p><p>USAF F-16C</p><p>USAF HH-60G</p><p>RNLAF F-16AM</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Non-NATO</strong></p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p>No facilities were defended in the North Sea as the exercises used simulated military targets which did not physically exist.</p><p> </p><p>No maritime patrol aircraft took part in the training.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-09-15T15:13:08.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417591/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417591/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417591/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-08","Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assets were involved in the Triplex Warrior exercise from (a) the UK, (b) NATO members and (c) non-NATO members in the (i) 2015 and (ii) 2014 exercise; what facilities in the North Sea were defended in the exercise; and if any maritime patrol aircraft took part.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","9435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417592","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-15","<p>The incident involving a Royal Navy (RN) submarine and the Fishing Vessel Karen took place on 15 April 2015. No other RN vessels were in the area at the time. On information available at the time, the RN was confident that no UK submarine was involved.</p><p>Detailed analysis of operational records is routine and this revealed that a UK submarine was involved in this incident. The submarine was not aware of the incident at the time and, therefore, did not surface.</p><p>Once this new information was confirmed, the Secretary of State for Defence, my right hon. Friend, the Member for Sevenoaks (Michael Fallon) was informed on 6 August.</p><p>During August, I held meetings to establish the facts, question the RN and discuss changes to policy to ensure the safety of fishing vessels. I then took the earliest opportunity to inform the House and put the public record straight on 7 September.</p><p>The RN is conducting an investigation of the circumstance surrounding this incident. Consideration will be given in due course to the information that could be released, within the bounds of operational security.</p><p>I am withholding further information as its disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","9421 ; 9422 ; 9423 ; 9568","2015-09-15T15:15:15.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417592/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417592/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417592/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-08","Submarines: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when the results of the Board of Inquiry into the incident involving a submarine and the fishing vessel Karen will be published.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","9420"
