"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417738","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-16","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and is campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Officials regularly meet with a range of external organisations to discuss the Government's objectives in Europe. <br></p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-09-16T16:43:31.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417738/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417738/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417738/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Ministry of Justice: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, which external organisations officials in his Department have met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many meetings such officials have had with each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417739","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-16","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and is campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. The Secretary of State regularly meets with a range of external organisations to discuss the Government's objectives in Europe. Details of Ministerial meetings with external organisations are published quarterly.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-09-16T16:47:42.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417739/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417739/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417739/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Ministry of Justice: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, which external organisations he has met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many times he has met each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417740","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-16","<p /> <p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and is campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Departments are appropriately resourced to support the Governmentâs priorities in Europe.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-09-16T16:41:28.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417740/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417740/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417740/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Ministry of Justice: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many officials in his Department are engaged in research into the effects of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9506"
