"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417745","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-16","<p>The prisoner referred to in my reply to Question 6617, is serving a life sentence for murder. Since May 2014, prisoners with a history of escape, absconding or serious temporary release failure during the current sentence have been precluded from transfer to open conditions, other than in the most exceptional circumstances. The decision to permit the prisoner to return to open conditions was taken only after careful consideration by senior officials within the National Offender Management Service in consultation with Ministers.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-09-16T14:58:33.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417745/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417745/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417745/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Open Prisons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 30 July 2015 to Question 6617, which offences the prisoner currently in an open prison who had previously absconded but was allowed to move to open conditions since May 2014 had committed; and what length of sentence was being served in each such case.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417746","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-16","<p /> <p>An update will be published in due course.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-09-16T14:48:07.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417746/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417746/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417746/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 21 July 2015 to Question 6753, what estimate he has made of the duration of the development period referred to in that Answer.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9554"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417747","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p>On 11 June we announced the start of the post-implementation review of the introduction of fees in the Employment Tribunals on the Ministry of Justice website. We have received a range of views and evidence from a variety of sources and are giving all relevant material the appropriate consideration.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","9433","2015-09-14T15:31:10.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417747/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417747/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417747/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Employment Tribunals Service: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what recent representations he has received on his Department's review of employment tribunal fees.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417748","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-16","<p>An internal review was commissioned into the case of Ross Underwood. It reported in July 2015 and all recommendations were accepted. Mr Underwood was recaptured on 2 June and returned to closed conditions. He received a 6 month sentence for absconding.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-09-16T14:24:01.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417748/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417748/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417748/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Spring Hill Prison: Prisoner Escapes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether an internal review has been conducted of the case of Ross Underwood who absconded from HMP Springhill in May 2015; and if he will make statement.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417749","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-16","<p /> <p>The changes we are making to criminal legal aid will deliver value for money to taxpayers and do not affect the availability of high quality legal advice to those who need it most. Changes will put the profession on a sustainable footing for the long term. Maintaining access to justice is absolutely vital. Even after these reforms our legal aid system remains one of the most generous systems in the world.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-09-16T16:37:42.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417749/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417749/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417749/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Legal Aid Scheme: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what his reasons are for reducing the legal aid budget.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417750","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-11","<p>No decision has been taken to close Bury Magistratesâ Court.</p><p> </p><p>We will consider all identified impacts and costs once the consultation closes and all responses have been fully analysed.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","9476","2015-09-11T13:43:12.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417750/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417750/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417750/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Magistrates' Courts: Bury","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will assess the effects on the (a) cost and (b) duration of journeys between prison and court of the closure of Bury Magistrates' Court.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417751","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-11","<p>No decision has been taken to close Bury Magistratesâ Court.</p><p> </p><p>Manchester and Salford Magistratesâ Court has 18 court rooms and operated at approximately 60% utilisation in 14/15, with 40% of its capacity being unused (8,928 hours). Bury Magistratesâ Court carried out 5,026 hours of criminal work in 2014/15 which is proposed to move to Manchester and Salford Magistratesâ Court.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-09-11T13:47:15.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417751/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417751/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417751/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Magistrates' Courts: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much unused (a) physical courtroom capacity and (b) court time there is at Manchester and Salford Magistrates' Court in the last year; and what assessment he has made of the adequacy of unused capacity at Manchester and Salford Magistrates' Court to accommodate current levels of work at Bury Magistrates' Court.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9477"
