ament.uk/resources/417766/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417766/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417766/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Employment Tribunals Service: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many applications for employment tribunal fee remission were (a) received and (b) awarded in each month since the introduction of tribunal fees.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417767","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-14","<p>The number of escapes and absconds from prison have fallen to record lows since 2010. Only one prisoner serving a sentence for murder has escaped from a closed prison in the last 5 years and the prisoner was recaptured the following day. There was a thorough investigation and as a result substantial changes were made to further improve security.</p><p>Absconds from open prisons are down 75% over the last ten years but each and every incident is taken seriously. We are not complacent and offenders who abscond are returned to closed prison conditions.</p><p>The table attached provides details of escapes and absconds between 1 April 2009 and 31 March 2014 of offenders serving a sentence for murder.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-10-14T15:26:28.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417767/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417767/answer","9484 - Philip Davies - Absconds and Escapes table.xls","Absconds & Escapes  1 April 2009  to 31 March 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417767/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Prisoner Escapes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 30 June 2015 to Question 3603, how many offenders serving a sentence for murder (a) absconded and (b) escaped; and in what circumstances those offenders absconded or escaped in each case.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9484"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417768","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-11","<p>The Department does not hold information requested. Annual costs of administering employment tribunal fee remission applications and annual administration costs of the employment tribunal fee scheme form part of the wider costs of operating and administering the Employment Tribunals. In 2014/15, the full cost for operating the Employment Tribunalsâ was Â£71.4m.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","9464","2015-09-11T12:23:51.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417768/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417768/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417768/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Employment Tribunals Service: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the annual administration costs of the employment tribunal fee scheme.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417769","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-16","<p>I attach a list of each of the prisons from which prisoners have been released on temporary licence (ROTL) in the last 5 years.</p><p>Eligibility for ROTL primarily depends upon the assessment of the prisoner in question rather than the classification of the establishment in which they are currently detained. So, whilst a Category A prisoner cannot have ROTL and Category B prisoners can take it only in exceptional circumstances, lower category prisoners who are eligible to be considered for ROTL are held in category B and in some category A prisons. The key test is whether the prisoner in question is eligible to be considered, has a legitimate purpose for temporary releases linked to the sentence plan, and passes the rigorous risk assessment required.</p><p>Since 2013 when the process was revised there has been a 39% drop in the number of temporary release failures. This is the lowest failure rate since 2002, and the absconding rate has reached record lows under this and the Coalition government.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-09-16T15:17:09.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417769/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417769/answer","9485 - table.xlsx","Temporary licence releases Jan 2011 - March 2015","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417769/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Prisoners' Release","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, in what proportion of (a) men's and (b) women's prisons are prisoners eligible for release on temporary licence.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417770","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-16","<p /> <p>10 defendants were proceeded against at magistrates' courts, and five were found guilty at all courts of offences related to dog fighting in England and Wales, in 2014.</p><p> </p><p>This information was obtained from a manual review of court case files that centrally held data indicated may be relevant, and as such has not been through the same quality assurance processes as for routinely published data.</p><p> </p><p>These figures relate to persons for whom these offences were the principal offences for which they were dealt with. When a defendant has been found guilty of two or more offences it is the offence for which the heaviest penalty is imposed. Where the same disposal is imposed for two or more offences, the offence selected is the offence for which the statutory maximum penalty is the most severe.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-09-16T14:28:44.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417770/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417770/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417770/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Dog Fighting: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many (a) prosecutions and (b) convictions there were for dog fighting in 2014.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417771","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-29","<p>The number of absconds has reduced by 75% over the last 10 years. There were 181 absconds in 2014/15, one of the lowest annual totals on record. The annual number of absconds from prison is published at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-and-probation-performance-statistics-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-and-probation-performance-statistics-2014-to-2015</a></p><br /><p>Open prisons provide an effective means of ensuring prisoners are tested in the community before they are released and to demonstrate a reduction in risk in preparation for release. To release prisoners directly from a closed prison without the resettlement benefits of the open estate would undoubtedly lead to higher levels of post-release re-offending.</p><br /><p>The table below provides a monthly breakdown of absconds that occurred during 2014/15, the most recent period that statistics are available.</p><br /><p>Table 1: <strong>Absconds from prisons, England and Wales, 2014/15 by month</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Month</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of absconds</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr-14</p></td><td><p>26</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May-14</p></td><td><p>17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jun-14</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul-14</p></td><td><p>22</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Aug-14</p></td><td><p>13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sep-14</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct-14</p></td><td><p>21</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nov-14</p></td><td><p>13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dec-14</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan-15</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Feb-15</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mar-15</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>181</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Notes:</p><p>Figures do not include absconds from NOMS-run immigration removal centres.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-10-29T17:21:16.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417771/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417771/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417771/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-08","Prisoner Escapes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many absconds from prison occurred in each month of the most recent year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417772","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Departments are appropriately resourced to support the Governmentâs priorities in Europe.</p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-09-15T10:00:24.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417772/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417772/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417772/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-08","Northern Ireland Office: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many officials in her Department are engaged in research into the effects of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417773","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Details of Ministerial meetings with external organisations are published quarterly.</p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-09-15T10:01:34.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417773/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417773/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417773/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-08","Northern Ireland Office: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, which external organisations she has met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many times she has met each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417774","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation: it believes it can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis. Officials regularly meet with a range of external organisations.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-09-15T10:03:00.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417774/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417774/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417774/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-08","Northern Ireland Office: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, which external organisations officials in her Department have met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many meetings such officials have had with each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9525"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417775","Prime Minister","false","2015-09-11","<p>Details of my meetings with external organisations are published on a quarterly basis and are available via the gov.uk website.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-09-11T12:56:27.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417775/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417775/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417775/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-09-08","Prime Minister: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, which external organisations he has met to discuss the consequences of the UK leaving the EU in each of the last three years; and how many times he has met each such organisation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","9544"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417776","Prime Minister","false","2015-09-14","<p>As I said during my oral statement on Syria: Refugees and Counter-Terrorism on 7 September 2015, <em>Official Report</em>, column 23, these individuals presented a clear and present danger to the country and this action was taken because there was no alternative. The Attorney General was consulted and was clear there was a legal basis for this action in international law. Our Permanent Representative has informed the President of the United Nations Security Council of this activity, which was conducted in the self-defence of the UK.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","9653 ; 9656","2015-09-14T15:49:25.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417776/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417776/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417776/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-09-08","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, whether the Government has carried out a cross-departmental assessment of the strategic implications of the targeted killing of British citizens outside declared war zones.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","9571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417777","Prime Minister","false","2015-09-14","<p>As I said during my oral statement on Syria: Refugees and Counter-Terrorism on 7 September 2015, <em>Official Report</em>, column 23, these individuals presented a clear and present danger to the country and this action was taken because there was no alternative. The Attorney General was consulted and was clear there was a legal basis for this action in international law. Our Permanent Representative has informed the President of the United Nations Security Council of this activity, which was conducted in the self-defence of the UK.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","9571 ; 9653","2015-09-14T15:49:27.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417777/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417777/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417777/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-09-08","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what assessment he has made of whether the Caroline principles on the right to self-defence under Article 51 of the UN Charter have been strictly applied by the UK Government.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","9656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417778","Prime Minister","false","2015-09-14","<p>I refer the hon. Member to my oral statement on Syria: Refugees and Counter-Terrorism on 7 September 2015, <em>Official Report</em>, column 23.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-09-14T15:45:28.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417778/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417778/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417778/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-09-08","Libya and Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if he will ensure that there is a debate in the House before further UK military intervention is taken in (a) Syria and (b) Libya.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","9655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417779","Cabinet Office","false","2015-09-11","<p>The 2015 National Security Strategy and the Strategic Defence and Security Review, informed by the National Security Risk Assessment, are considering a wide range of risks and threats including terrorism, and responses. We cannot speculate on the outcome of the Strategic Defence and Security Review.</p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2015-09-11T11:29:04.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417779/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417779/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417779/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-09-08","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if the Government will devise and disclose a distinct UK drones and targeted killing policy as part of the Strategic Defence and Security Review.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","9637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417780","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Prime Minister and I are ready to take military action as a last resort to prevent an imminent terrorist attack on the UK.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-09-14T15:50:38.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417780/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417780/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417780/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-08","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Government has compiled a list of people for targeted killing outside Iraq.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","9654"
