"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417811","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-14","<p /> <p>The Government has carefully considered all measures introduced in the Summer Budget.</p><p> </p><p>This Government is committed to reducing child poverty, and ensuring everyone has the opportunity to get on in life.</p><p> </p><p>As part of this we are introducing new life chances measures to drive action on addressing the root causes of disadvantage.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-09-14T11:25:40.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417811/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417811/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417811/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-08","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the effect on (a) relative and (b) absolute child poverty of the four-year freeze announced in the July Budget on the uprating of (i) jobseeker's allowance and (ii) employment and support allowance.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","9628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417812","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-11","<p /> <p>The law requires employers to enrol all eligible workers into a qualifying workplace pension scheme and make at least a minimum contribution to their pension. This includes workers employed through employment agencies. The Department has made no separate assessment of the impact of automatic enrolment on these workers.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-11T11:18:34.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417812/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417812/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417812/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-08","Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of automatic-enrolment pension arrangements on workers employed through employment agencies.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","9646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417813","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-11","<p /> <p>We have implemented a wide range of initiatives across the whole Personal Independence Payment (PIP) claim journey to speed up processes and are continuing to identify further opportunities for improvement. Figures released on 17 June reflect the significant progress made over the past year and show claims for PIP are now being cleared at four times the rate they were in January 2014. These figures can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-independence-payment-april-2013-to-april-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-independence-payment-april-2013-to-april-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>The latest statistics show that as at April 2015 a new claimant was waiting on average (median) 11 weeks from the point of registration to a decision being made on their claim (end to end), compared to 41 weeks in July 2014. DLA reassessment claims were taking on average (median) 10 weeks in April 2015.</p><p> </p><p>Updated statistics on PIP registrations, clearances, clearance times and outstanding times (up to July 2015 data) are due to be published and can be found from 16th September at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-independence-payment-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-independence-payment-statistics</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-11T13:53:33.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417813/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417813/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417813/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-08","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what progress has been made on addressing the backlog in applications for personal independence payments; and for what median end-to-end time applicants are currently waiting.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","9645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417814","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-11","<p /> <p>No representations have been received from the UN Special Rapporteur.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-11T13:45:59.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417814/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417814/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417814/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-08","Social Security Benefits: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what representations he has received from the UN Special Rapporteur on disabled rights on an investigation into welfare reforms since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","9461"
