"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417822","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-11","<p /> <p>The Welfare Cap of Annually Managed Expenditure (AME) has been set for this Parliament, at the level of the Office for Budget Responsibilityâs Summer 2015 forecast for spending in scope of the Cap.</p><p> </p><p>This amounts to: Â£115.2bn in 2016-17; Â£114.6bn in 2017-18; Â£114.0bn in 2018-19; Â£113.5bn in 2019-20; and Â£114.9bn in 2020-21.</p><p> </p><p>The Welfare Cap is not assessed at a sub-national level.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-09-11T11:50:47.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417822/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417822/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417822/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-08","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the effect of the welfare cap will be in (a) Wellingborough and (b) England.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","9590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417823","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-24","<p>Representations regarding the removal of the spare room subsidy are received from Hon. Members of all parties, interest groups and members of the public.</p><p> </p><p>No central record is kept of the number of representations made, including those specifically made by individuals who identify themselves as members of the Conservative Party.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested is therefore not available.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-24T15:19:05.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417823/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417823/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417823/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-08","Housing Benefit: Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many representations he has received from hon. Members from the Conservative Party on the under-occupancy penalty.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417824","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-11","<p /> <p>The Government set out its assessment of the impacts of the policies in the Welfare Reform and Work Bill on 20th July. A link to the impact assessment is included.</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/documents/impact-assessments/IA15-006.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/documents/impact-assessments/IA15-006.pdf</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-11T14:26:41.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417824/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417824/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417824/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-08","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what equality impact assessment of the recent change to the benefits cap his Department has undertaken.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","9474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417825","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-14","<p /> <p>The Rules of Procedure of the UN Committee on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities provide that all documents and proceedings of the Committee relating to the conduct of an inquiry under the Optional Protocol are confidential. However, as the existence of an inquiry has already been made public by others, I can confirm that the Government has received representations from the Committee in connection with that. The nature, scope and timetable for the inquiry remain confidential.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-14T14:26:35.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417825/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417825/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417825/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-08","Social Security Benefits: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what representations he has received from the UN Committee on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities on an investigation into welfare reforms since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","9424"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417826","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-11","<p /> <p>Details of the highest amount of annual housing benefit paid to a single household in each of the last five years can be found using the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a></p><p> </p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html</a></p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-11T10:20:12.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417826/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417826/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417826/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-08","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the highest amount of annual housing benefit paid to a single household was in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418546","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-14","<p>We are committed to delivering 275,000 affordable homes by 2020. This will be the fastest rate of affordable house building in the last 20 years.</p><p> </p><p>The Affordable Homes Programme is open and receiving bids. We have already allocated Â£1 billion.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-09-14T16:11:27.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418546/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418546/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418546/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Social Rented Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to encourage the building of homes for social rent.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","901320"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418547","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Productivity Plan published in July sets out ambitious plans to further streamline the planning process. This includes making it easier to establish the principle of development, streamline the length and process for Local Plans and introducing a new dispute resolution process for section 106 agreements.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-09-14T16:10:41.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418547/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418547/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418547/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to speed up the planning process.","false","Biography information for Kevin Hollinrake","Thirsk and Malton","Kevin Hollinrake","901317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418548","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-14","<p>Planning authorities are required to plan for a mix of housing to cater for the needs of different groups in their communities, including people with disabilities. The Government has an ongoing dialogue with a range of stakeholders to assess the effectiveness of the Framework.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2015-09-14T16:09:30.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418548/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418548/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418548/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Housing: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the National Planning Policy Framework in addressing the housing needs of disabled people.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","901319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418549","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-14","<p>My rt. hon. Friend, the Home Secretary and I are leading a Joint Committee â the Ministerial Group on Syrian Refugees â to put in place the necessary arrangements to resettle 20,000 Syrian refugees over the course of this Parliament. Representatives from the Local Government Association attended the first meeting of this Group on Friday. Other key partners such as charities and faith institutions will also have the opportunity to contribute.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2015-09-14T16:15:11.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418549/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418549/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418549/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with local government leaders on the provision of (a) housing and (b) other council assistance for refugees.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","901300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418550","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-14","<p>My Department publishes figures on spending power for all local authorities each year, which includes both central government and locally-raised funding.</p><p>Together with other Departments we are using the Spending Review to consider the level of funding for local government and have invited representations from interest groups including local authorities.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2015-09-14T16:16:11.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418550/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418550/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418550/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-08","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent comparative assessment he has made of (a) the level of funding for and (b) the costs of local authorities.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","901305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416929","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-09-22","<p>The minutes of the meeting of the 20 May have been published. They were published on 23 July 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2015-09-22T09:38:56.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416929/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416929/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416929/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-09-07","Expert Committee on Pesticides","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government why the Expert Committee on Pesticides has not published the minutes of its meeting of 20 May; and what assessment they have made of whether, by not publishing those minutes, the Committee has breached its terms of reference.","false","Biography information for Baroness Parminter",,"Baroness Parminter","HL1849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416930","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Commission has begun a review of the science relating to neonicotinoids and bees. This will include effects on bees from seed treatment and granule uses of the restricted neonicotinoids on any crop. The Government will contribute fully to this review and will base its view on future regulation of neonicotinoids on all the available scientific evidence. We are aware that there have been a number of new studies since 2013. Initial results from a large field trial being carried out by the Centre for Ecology and Hydrology to look at honey bees, bumble bees and solitary bees are expected later this year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK Expert Committee on Pesticides has the task of advising Ministers on issues relating to the authorisation of pesticides. It considered recent research on neonicotinoids and pollinators, including the recent report by RundlÃ¶f et al, at its May 2015 meeting. The detailed record of the meeting states that the Committee âagreed that this was a complex and evolving issue that required careful judgement, based on a weight of evidence approachâ. The Committee agreed to come back to the issue regularly at future meetings.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2015-09-15T11:23:17.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416930/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416930/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416930/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-09-07","Oilseed Rape: Neonicotinoids","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government what assessment they have made of recent field trials of rape seed treated with neonicotinoids and the impact of neonicotinoids on bumblebee populations.","false","Biography information for Baroness Parminter",,"Baroness Parminter","HL1850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416931","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-09-15","<p>The decision was taken on 21 July and was communicated to the applicant on 22 July. Details of pesticide authorisations issued are placed on the Health and Safety Executive website. These authorisations were issued to the National Farmersâ Union on 24 July and were placed on the website on the same day.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2015-09-15T12:18:07.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416931/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416931/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416931/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-09-07","Oilseed Rape: Neonicotinoids","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government on what date they took the decision to grant an emergency application from the National Farmersâ Union to use neonicotinoid seed treatments in the autumn of 2015; when this decision was announced; and, if there was a gap between the date of decision and date of announcement, what was the reason for the delay.","false","Biography information for Baroness Parminter",,"Baroness Parminter","HL1851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416932","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-09-17","<p>The Expert Committee on Pesticides published the agenda for the 7 July meeting and the minutes of its meeting of 20 May on 23 July 2015.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2015-09-17T16:14:23.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416932/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416932/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416932/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-09-07","Expert Committee on Pesticides","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government why the Expert Committee on Pesticides has not published the agenda for its meeting on 7 July and the minutes of its meeting on 20 May; and what involvement they had, if any, in the decision not to publish those documents.","false","Biography information for Lord Strasburger",,"Lord Strasburger","HL1852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416933","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-09-16","<p>The Government is committed to openness and transparency, in particular in relation to scientific advice. The Code of Practice for Scientific Advisory Committees sets out principles upon which departments and SACs set their own publication policy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Defraâs Scientific Advisory Council, and Scientific Advisory Committees, may choose not to publish their agendas or minutes when they relate to:</p><p> </p><p>Â· confidential information;</p><p> </p><p>Â· there is non-disclosure associated with the meeting subject material;</p><p> </p><p>Â· Government Security Classified documents; or</p><p> </p><p>Â· commercially sensitive information.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This decision to do so is assessed against the Code of Practice for Scientific Advisory Committees. A publicly available explanation is provided when Committees decide not to publish minutes.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In assessing whether grounds for not publishing comply with the Code of Practiceâs need for transparency, the committee considers:</p><p> </p><p>Â· public interest in the subject material;</p><p> </p><p>Â· the commercial impact should the material be published;</p><p> </p><p>Â· the timing of the material be published; and</p><p> </p><p>Â· the policy impact, for example, in relation to UK negotiations with another country.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2015-09-16T12:40:18.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416933/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416933/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416933/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-09-07","Scientific Advisers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government on what grounds scientific advisory committees may choose not to publish their agendas and minutes; and what assessment they have made of whether such grounds comply with the need for transparency set out in the Code of Practice for Scientific Advisory Committees.","false","Biography information for Lord Strasburger",,"Lord Strasburger","HL1853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416934","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-14","<p /> <p>This information is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>",,"Lord Freud",,"2015-09-14T13:45:01.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416934/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416934/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416934/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-07","Government Departments: Marketing","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government how many times this year the Department for Work and Pensions hasâ¯published invented quotes and stock images purporting to be from and ofâ¯real benefits claimants; and to what extentâ¯other government departments engage in similar practices.","false","Biography information for Lord Strasburger",,"Lord Strasburger","HL1854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416935","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-09-21","<p>Where development is proposed and requires a planning application, local planning authorities have broad powers to impose conditions and enforce where they consider that conditions have been breached. Conditions must meet the policy test in the National Planning Policy Framework which states that planning conditions should only be imposed where they are necessary, relevant to planning and to the development to be permitted, enforceable, precise and reasonable in all other respects. Whether enforcement action against breach of a condition is justified is a matter of their discretion for Local Planning Authorities.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford","HL1856 ; HL1857 ; HL1858 ; HL1859 ; HL1860","2015-09-21T15:09:06.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416935/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416935/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416935/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-07","Network Rail: Planning Permission","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government whether the Town and Country Planning Act 1990, or any other legislation, confers on local planning authorities powers to enforce conditions that they have imposed upon Network Rail when approving a planning application.","false","Biography information for Lord Krebs",,"Lord Krebs","HL1855"
