"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417147","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-15","<p>UK Export Finance has been participating in discussions within the OECD with the aim of achieving a multilateral agreement on limiting the provision of export credits for coal-fired power projects.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-09-15T11:02:00.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417147/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417147/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417147/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-07","Coal: Export Credit Guarantees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to secure an agreement between OECD countries to stop supporting all coal projects overseas through export credit agencies.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","9260"
