"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417159","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Government Office for Science Foresight programme is directed by Sir Mark Walport, Government Chief Scientific Advisor. Foresight projects examine either an important public policy issue where science might be part of the solution, or a scientific topic where potential applications and technologies are yet to be realised. Foresightâs two current projects are 'Future of an ageing population' and âFuture of citiesâ. The Government Office for Science actively considers topics for future projects, and welcomes suggestions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-09-15T16:42:57.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417159/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417159/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417159/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-07","Government Office for Science","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what plans he has for future projects under the Foresight Project of the Government Office for Science.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","9280"
